cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the automatic detection of liver lesions in CT images using deep learning. The use of a multi-class convolutional neural network (CNN) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of image processing techniques and medical imaging data could also suggest the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of prior knowledge of the data and the potential application in supporting radiologists could suggest the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
